"title": "5971: uniqueness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5971: uniqueness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The quality of being without an equal. Scripture stresses the uniqueness of God and of the salvation that is available only from him. Jesus Christ is the unique mediator between God and humanity.</p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:25\">ISA 40:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:10\">EXO 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:2\">1SA 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:18\">ISA 40:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15-1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:15–6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:25\">JUD 1:25</a></p>\n<h3>As a forgiver of sins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:7\">MRK 2:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of the Trinity</h2>\n<h3>The three persons are distinct</h3>\n<p>All use the first person singular pronoun:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:28\">JHN 12:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:4\">JHN 17:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:6\">1CO 12:4–12:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:5\">EPH 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>God is one</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6\">ISA 44:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:5-Isa45:6\">ISA 45:5–45:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:6\">EPH 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:9\">JAS 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>There is plurality in the Godhead</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:22\">GEN 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:5-Gen11:7\">GEN 11:5–11:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8\">ISA 6:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:20\">MAT 28:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a></p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>As God's Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote “only begotten” indicates that Jesus Christ is the unique Son of God, in origin, eternity and nature.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:3\">HEB 1:1–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>As the mediator between God and humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:6\">HEB 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>As the sacrifice for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:10\">ROM 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:14\">HEB 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:18\">HEB 10:18</a></p>\n<h3>As the Saviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:12\">ACT 4:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:12\">1JN 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>As the foundation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:11\">1CO 3:11</a></p>\n<h2>The uniqueness of Scripture</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:15-2Tim3:16\">2TI 3:15–3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:18-Rev22:19\">REV 22:18–22:19</a></p>\n<h2>Each human being is unique</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:13-Ps139:16\">PSA 139:13–139:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15\">GAL 1:15</a></p>\n<h2>Each believer is unique</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:17\">REV 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1\">ISA 43:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:3\">JHN 10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:3\">1CO 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:21\">1CO 12:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:9\">GAL 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:19\">2TI 2:19</a></p>",
